en_219485_0	The CID submitted a motion to courts yesterday with regard to investigations conducted into arrested Dr. Safi Siyabdeen.
en_219485_1	The motion requests permission for 147 mothers who claim they have been sterilised to undergo the H.S.G test.
en_219485_2	Previously the CID had requested for approval, however owing to the protest of lawyers appearing on behalf of the plaintiff, the court proceedings were postponed to 11th of July.
en_219485_3	Meanwhile, during a media briefing held in Colombo yesterday MP Udaya Gammanpila expressed his views further regarding the matter.
en_219485_4	He noted that a presidents commission should be appointed to investigate into this incident.
